      "type": "html",
      "id": "515ad688166ec7d3",
      "text": "<h3>Longitudinal</h3>\n\n\"They could then gather various forms of evidence in order to identify and test successful and promising approaches and determine the factors inhibiting change and how these might be circumvented and how to foster further developments. It takes time to reliably establish what kinds of policies, procedures and practices result in significant change and improved learning outcomes. So, such longitudinal and collaborative researchwould need to run for several years, but it would yield far more illuminating findings than many of the current studies and would be far more likely to influence planners, managers and practitioners, <strong>show how the potential of educational technology can be maximised and the problems of adop- tion and sustainability minimised</strong>.\" (p. 9)"
